Aerosmith - The Boys From Boston 1975.08.29 1CD 64 minutes FM FLAC 

The Boys From Boston 1975 (Magic Bus MB-07 E/F)
Schaeffer Music Festival, Wollman Skating Rink, Central Park, New York City – August 29, 1975

The 1975 gig in Central Park from the Toys In The Attic tour is a famous one, for good reason, 
first and foremost is the recording. The concert was recorded by the King Biscuit Flower Hour 
(KBFH) so the quality is excellent. The band is at the height of the 70’s power as a live act.

Tracklist:
01 - Introduction
02 - Walkin' The Dog
03 - S.O.S. (Too Bad)
04 - Somebody
05 - Big Ten Inch Record
06 - Sweet Emotion
07 - Dream On
08 - Write Me A Letter
09 - Walk This Way
10 - No More No More
11 - Same Old Song And Dance
12 - The Train Kept A Rollin'
13 - Encore Break
14 - Toys In The Attic

Total Time = 64 minutes

Aerosmith:
Steven Tyler - Vocals
Joe Perry - Guitar
Brad Whitford - Guitar
Tom Hamilton - Bass
Joey Kramer - Drums
